</taxonomicName>
by the absence of heterogenous dorsal scales and short and thick nuchal scales.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98B30BFF94FF824FECFA8DFEC4F8C9" blockId="36.[151,1437,1009,2006]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824E68FA8DFE14FAC1" authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1843" box="[342,507,1297,1321]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824E68FA8DFE14FAC1" box="[342,507,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Psammophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be diagnosed from all other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824B37FA8DFB6BFAC2" box="[1033,1156,1297,1322]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Draconinae">draconinae</taxonomicName>
lizards from the Indian subcontinent except 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824EB9FAA9FDC4FAA5" baseAuthorityName="Hardwicke &amp; Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[391,555,1333,1357]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Calotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824EB9FAA9FDC4FAA5" box="[391,555,1333,1357]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Calotes minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in having a dorso-ventrally compressed body. 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824B5EFAA9FAEAFAA5" authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1843" box="[1120,1285,1333,1357]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824B5EFAA9FAEAFAA5" box="[1120,1285,1333,1357]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Psammophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824FA9FAC5FED4FA99" baseAuthorityName="Hardwicke &amp; Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[151,315,1369,1393]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Calotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824FA9FAC5FED4FA99" box="[151,315,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Calotes minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having small body scales and higher number of around the body scales 80–150 (vs 48–60). 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824FA9FAE1FED3FA7D" authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1843" box="[151,316,1405,1429]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824FA9FAE1FED3FA7D" box="[151,316,1405,1429]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Psammophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterized by a medium to large adult body size (SVL mm to mm); body dorso-ventrally compressed; presence of an antehumeral fold; supratympanic spines present, reduced in size; dorsal and lateral scales rows slightly irregular; nuchal and dorsal crest small, reduced; dorsal and lateral scales small, keeled, scale rows directed postero-dorsally. 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824EC3FA75FD4DF9E9" authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1843" box="[509,674,1513,1537]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824EC3FA75FD4DF9E9" box="[509,674,1513,1537]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Psammophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from its sister genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824BB0FA75FAC7F9E9" authority="Pal &amp; Vijayakumar &amp; Shanker &amp; Jayarajan &amp; Deepak, 2018" authorityName="Pal &amp; Vijayakumar &amp; Shanker &amp; Jayarajan &amp; Deepak" authorityYear="2018" box="[1166,1320,1513,1537]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Monilesaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824BB0FA75FAC7F9E9" box="[1166,1320,1513,1537]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Monilesaurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A260D262FF94FF824A0FFA75FA73F9E9" box="[1329,1436,1513,1538]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824A0FFA75FA7AF9EA" bold="true" box="[1329,1429,1513,1538]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824FF6F991FEF1F9CD" box="[200,286,1549,1573]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Calotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824FF6F991FEF1F9CD" box="[200,286,1549,1573]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Calotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a dorso-ventrally compressed body (vs dorso-laterally compressed) and higher number of scales on the mid-body scales (more than 80 vs less than 65) and reduced nuchal crest (vs. well developed); and from 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824FE8F9CAFEBCF985" authority="Pal &amp; Vijayakumar &amp; Shanker &amp; Jayarajan &amp; Deepak, 2018" authorityName="Pal &amp; Vijayakumar &amp; Shanker &amp; Jayarajan &amp; Deepak" authorityYear="2018" box="[214,339,1622,1645]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Microauris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824FE8F9CAFEBCF985" box="[214,339,1622,1645]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Microauris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A260D262FF94FF824E62F9C9FE28F986" box="[348,455,1621,1646]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824E62F9C9FE28F986" bold="true" box="[348,455,1621,1646]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">gen. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having a relatively large tympanum (
<figureCitation id="131CAF8EFF94FF824CA2F9C9FC00F986" box="[924,1007,1621,1646]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1517,1539]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,589,1496]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[152,1435,589,1496]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. Lateral close-up of head characteristics of the four sister clades A. Calotes, B. Microauris, C. Monilesaurus and D. Psammophilus. Scale bar: 10 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1440692/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Fig. 9d</figureCitation>
vs 9b). Scales on head large uniform shield like (vs small, sub-triangular) (
<figureCitation id="131CAF8EFF94FF824D6FF9E5FD5DF97A" box="[593,690,1657,1682]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1428,1450]" captionTargetBox="[194,1389,487,1372]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[191,1395,483,1390]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 10. Dorsal and ventral close-ups of head characteristics of the four sister clades A., E. Monilesaurus; B., F. Calotes; C., G. Psammophilus; and D., H. Microauris." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1440694/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Fig. 10c</figureCitation>
vs 10d). Supratympanic spines are present, in the form of two separated spines vs clusters in 
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824ECFF901FD15F95D" box="[497,762,1693,1717]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824ECFF901FDA5F95D" box="[497,586,1693,1717]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Calotes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Calotes</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824D6BF901FD15F95D" authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1843" box="[597,762,1693,1717]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Psammophilus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
are sexually dimorphic, adult males are larger than females and have enlarged cheeks. 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824EECF95DFD98F931" authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1843" box="[466,631,1729,1753]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824EECF95DFD98F931" box="[466,631,1729,1753]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Psammophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are also sexually dichromatic; during breeding season males acquire bright yellow and orange colors on the dorsum while females remain dull to dark brown with or without orange/ yellow spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98B30BFF94FF824FF9F8B1FC6EF83E" blockId="36.[151,1437,1009,2006]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824FF9F8B1FE3EF8AE" bold="true" box="[199,465,1837,1862]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Taxonomic comments.</emphasis>
The two species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824DAAF8B1FC76F8AD" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[660,921,1837,1861]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dorsalis">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824DAAF8B1FC76F8AD" box="[660,921,1837,1861]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Psammophilus dorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824CEEF8B1FAFFF8AD" baseAuthorityName="Stoliczka" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[976,1296,1837,1861]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blanfordanus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824CEEF8B1FAFFF8AD" box="[976,1296,1837,1861]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Psammophilus blanfordanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were earlier placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824EBBF8CEFD60F882" authority="(Daudin, 1802)" authorityName="Daudin" authorityYear="1802" baseAuthorityName="Daudin" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[389,655,1873,1898]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Agama" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824EBBF8CEFE3BF881" box="[389,468,1874,1897]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Agama</emphasis>
(Daudin, 1802)
</taxonomicName>
and the now obsolete genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824CD5F8CDFB1BF882" authority="(Gray, 1845)" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[1003,1268,1873,1898]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Charasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824CD5F8CDFBBCF881" box="[1003,1107,1873,1897]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Charasia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6CEFAFF94FF824B58F8CEFB03F882" box="[1126,1260,1873,1898]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" refId="ref35213" refString="Gray, E. (1845) Catalogue of the specimens of lizards in the collection British museum. Trustees of die British Museum / Edward Newman, London, 289 pp." type="book">Gray, 1845</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6CEFAFF94FF824A3DF8CDFA73F882" box="[1283,1436,1873,1898]" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" refId="ref37909" refString="Smith, M. A. (1935) The Fauna of British India, Including Ceylon and Burma; Reptilia and Amphibia. Fol. II. Sauria. Taylor and Francis, London, 440 pp." type="book">Smith (1935)</bibRefCitation>
transferred the two species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824EF5F8E9FD7AF865" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1845" box="[459,661,1909,1933]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Charasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dorsalis">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824EF5F8E9FD7AF865" box="[459,661,1909,1933]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Charasia dorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824DF2F8E9FC3FF865" authorityName=", Boulenger" authorityYear="1885" box="[716,976,1909,1933]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Charasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blanfordanus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824DF2F8E9FC3FF865" box="[716,976,1909,1933]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Charasia blanfordanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824B56F8E9FAE2F865" authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1843" box="[1128,1293,1909,1933]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824B56F8E9FAE2F865" box="[1128,1293,1909,1933]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Psammophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Most likely due to their dorso-ventrally compressed body, 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824D9CF805FCA8F859" authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1843" box="[674,839,1945,1969]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF94FF824D9CF805FCA8F859" box="[674,839,1945,1969]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="437">Psammophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was placed among the 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824B6EF805FB2CF85A" box="[1104,1219,1945,1970]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Agaminae">Agaminae</taxonomicName>
but molecular data suggest that they are nested well within the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF94FF824DC6F821FC92F83E" box="[760,893,1981,2006]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="36" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Draconinae">Draconinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33DE080FF95FF834FF9FF0BFE8FFD88" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B98B30BFF95FF834FF9FF0BFB28FE8C" blockId="37.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
Both 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF95FF834E3AFF05FE95FF58" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1845" box="[260,378,152,176]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Charasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dorsalis">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834E3AFF05FE95FF58" box="[260,378,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">P. dorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF95FF834E8FFF05FD8FFF58" authorityName=", Boulenger" authorityYear="1885" box="[433,608,152,176]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Charasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blanfordanus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834E8FFF05FD8FFF58" box="[433,608,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">P. blanfordanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been recorded in the 
<collectingRegion id="49E37DE9FF95FF834CB0FF04FC06FF47" box="[910,1001,152,175]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Western" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Western</collectingRegion>
Ghats (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6CEFAFF95FF834B7FFF0BFB20FF58" box="[1089,1231,151,176]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" refId="ref37909" refString="Smith, M. A. (1935) The Fauna of British India, Including Ceylon and Burma; Reptilia and Amphibia. Fol. II. Sauria. Taylor and Francis, London, 440 pp." type="book">Smith, 1935</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6CEFAFF95FF834BDDFF0BFA73FF58" box="[1251,1436,151,176]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" refId="ref38213" refString="Stoliczka, F. (1871) Notes on new or little known Indian lizards. Proceedings of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, 9, 192 - 195." type="journal article">Stoliczka (1871)</bibRefCitation>
provided a brief description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF95FF834D3EFF21FD5DFF3C" authorityName=", Boulenger" authorityYear="1885" box="[512,690,188,212]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Charasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blanfordanus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834D3EFF21FD5DFF3C" box="[512,690,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">P. blanfordanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without mentioning a 
<typeStatus id="549C0DA9FF95FF834C84FF21FC05FF3D" box="[954,1002,189,213]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">type</typeStatus>
locality and later provided a detailed description (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6CEFAFF95FF834E1DFF43FE3AFF10" box="[291,469,223,248]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" refId="ref38243" refString="Stoliczka, F. (1872) Notes on various new or little known Indian lizards. Proceedings of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, 41, 86 - 135." type="journal article">Stoliczka, 1872</bibRefCitation>
) based on a large number of samples collected from central 
<collectingCountry id="F330F39BFF95FF834BB9FF43FB2EFF10" box="[1159,1217,223,248]" name="India" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">India</collectingCountry>
(Udaypore west of Chotanagpur, West of Raipore, West of Ranchi) which are currently recognized as 
<typeStatus id="549C0DA9FF95FF834B05FE99FB72FEF5" box="[1083,1181,261,285]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">syntypes</typeStatus>
in ZSI with additional 
<typeStatus id="549C0DA9FF95FF834FA9FEB4FF16FEA8" box="[151,249,296,320]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">syntypes</typeStatus>
in 
<collectionCode id="ED362BCEFF95FF834E17FEB4FE9EFED7" box="[297,369,296,319]" country="Austria" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/c7yt-hh77" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">NMW</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode id="ED362BCEFF95FF834E8AFEB4FE1EFED7" box="[436,497,296,319]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum f�r Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">ZMB</collectionCode>
(Das 
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834D7EFEB5FD98FEA8" box="[576,631,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">et al</emphasis>
. 1998). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6CEFAFF95FF834DDCFEBBFC4EFEA8" box="[738,929,295,320]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" refId="ref38243" refString="Stoliczka, F. (1872) Notes on various new or little known Indian lizards. Proceedings of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, 41, 86 - 135." type="journal article">Stoliczka (1872)</bibRefCitation>
also mentions that 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF95FF834BAAFEB5FAA5FEA8" authorityName=", Boulenger" authorityYear="1885" box="[1172,1354,296,320]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Charasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blanfordanus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834BAAFEB5FAA5FEA8" box="[1172,1354,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">P. blanfordanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not uncommon in Parisnath (Parasnath) hill. 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF95FF834D5CFED0FC88FE8C" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[610,871,332,356]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dorsalis">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834D5CFED0FC88FE8C" box="[610,871,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Psammophilus dorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Gray (1831).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98B30BFF95FF834FF9FEF3FE8FFD88" blockId="37.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
The key character to diagnose this species is number of scales around the body, which overlap with each other (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6CEFAFF95FF834FA0FE08FEB3FE45" box="[158,348,404,429]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" refId="ref34283" refString="Boulenger, G. A. (1885) Catalogue of lizards in the British museum. Fol. 1. Geckonidae, Eublepharidae, Uroplatidae, Pygopodidae, Agamidae, Second edition. British Museum (Natural History), London, 436 pp." type="book">Boulenger, 1885</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6CEFAFF95FF834E56FE08FE1BFE45" box="[360,500,404,429]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" refId="ref37909" refString="Smith, M. A. (1935) The Fauna of British India, Including Ceylon and Burma; Reptilia and Amphibia. Fol. II. Sauria. Taylor and Francis, London, 440 pp." type="book">Smith, 1935</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6CEFAFF95FF834D39FE08FD22FE45" box="[519,717,404,429]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" refId="ref34283" refString="Boulenger, G. A. (1885) Catalogue of lizards in the British museum. Fol. 1. Geckonidae, Eublepharidae, Uroplatidae, Pygopodidae, Agamidae, Second edition. British Museum (Natural History), London, 436 pp." type="book">Boulenger (1885)</bibRefCitation>
used a combination of specimens from 
<collectingRegion id="49E37DE9FF95FF834BB4FE08FB00FE45" box="[1162,1263,404,429]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Southern" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Southern</collectingRegion>
<collectingCountry id="F330F39BFF95FF834BC8FE08FADFFE45" box="[1270,1328,404,429]" name="India" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">India</collectingCountry>
(Nilgiris, Malabar, Madras and a few specimens with locality “ 
<collectingCountry id="F330F39BFF95FF834DCBFE2BFCDCFE38" box="[757,819,439,464]" name="India" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">India</collectingCountry>
”) to describe 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF95FF834CECFE25FBA6FE38" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[978,1097,440,464]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dorsalis">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834CECFE25FBA6FE38" box="[978,1097,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">P. dorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. To describe 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF95FF834BDAFE25FE8FFE1D" authority=", Boulenger (1885)" authorityName=", Boulenger" authorityYear="1885" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Charasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blanfordanus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834BDAFE25FA73FE38" box="[1252,1436,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">P. blanfordanus,</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6CEFAFF95FF834FA9FE40FE8FFE1D" box="[151,352,476,501]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" refId="ref34283" refString="Boulenger, G. A. (1885) Catalogue of lizards in the British museum. Fol. 1. Geckonidae, Eublepharidae, Uroplatidae, Pygopodidae, Agamidae, Second edition. British Museum (Natural History), London, 436 pp." type="book">Boulenger (1885)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
used specimens from Godavari valley and “Jeypore” (
<collectingRegion id="49E37DE9FF95FF834CE3FE40FBABFE1D" box="[989,1092,476,501]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Northern" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Northern</collectingRegion>
Andhra) and Ranchi (now in 
<collectingRegion id="49E37DE9FF95FF834FA9FE63FEE5FDF0" box="[151,266,511,536]" country="India" name="Jharkhand" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Jharkhand</collectingRegion>
state). One single specimen collected from Parasnath, 
<collectingRegion id="49E37DE9FF95FF834CACFE63FBEAFDF0" box="[914,1029,511,536]" country="India" name="Jharkhand" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Jharkhand</collectingRegion>
that is relatively close to the 
<typeStatus id="549C0DA9FF95FF834A52FD9CFA73FDF0" box="[1388,1436,512,536]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<collectingRegion id="49E37DE9FF95FF834FC4FDB8FEA1FDD5" box="[250,334,548,573]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Central" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Central</collectingRegion>
<collectingCountry id="F330F39BFF95FF834E68FDB8FE7EFDD5" box="[342,401,548,573]" name="India" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">India</collectingCountry>
) of 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF95FF834EFEFDB9FD9EFDD4" authorityName=", Boulenger" authorityYear="1885" box="[448,625,548,572]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Charasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blanfordanus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834EFEFDB9FD9EFDD4" box="[448,625,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">P. blanfordanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had 1–3% genetic divergence in the 16S gene from 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF95FF834BFDFDB9FAD5FDD4" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[1219,1338,548,572]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dorsalis">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834BFDFDB9FAD5FDD4" box="[1219,1338,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">P. dorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
samples used in this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33DE080FF95FF834FF9FDF1FC24FCFC" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B98B30BFF95FF834FF9FDF1FAB5FD18" blockId="37.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
We were unable to find 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF95FF834EE3FDF1FD60FD6C" authorityName=", Boulenger" authorityYear="1885" box="[477,655,620,644]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Charasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blanfordanus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834EE3FDF1FD60FD6C" box="[477,655,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">P. blanfordanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingRegion id="49E37DE9FF95FF834C3DFDF1FCB1FD6C" box="[771,862,621,644]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Western" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Western</collectingRegion>
Ghats during our fieldwork. Given the amount of morphological variation among the observed individuals and wide distribution of this group, we would suggest a thorough evaluation of this species group from the entire peninsula with detailed sampling. In the present work, we only describe 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF95FF834E0AFD45FE46FD18" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[308,425,728,752]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dorsalis">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834E0AFD45FE46FD18" box="[308,425,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">P. dorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as we were unable to confirm the presence of 
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF95FF834C8CFD45FB8DFD18" authorityName=", Boulenger" authorityYear="1885" box="[946,1122,728,752]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Charasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blanfordanus">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834C8CFD45FB8DFD18" box="[946,1122,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">P. blanfordanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<collectingRegion id="49E37DE9FF95FF834B91FD44FAE5FD07" box="[1199,1290,728,751]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Western" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Western</collectingRegion>
Ghats.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98B30BFF95FF834FF9FD60FC24FCFC" blockId="37.[151,1437,151,789]" box="[199,971,764,789]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834FF9FD60FED0FCFD" bold="true" box="[199,319,764,789]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Members.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF95FF834E78FD60FDA3FCFC" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[326,588,764,788]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dorsalis">
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834E78FD60FDA3FCFC" box="[326,588,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Psammophilus dorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B9536F19FF95FF834DBDFD60FC24FCFC" box="[643,971,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
<taxonomicName id="4C27C888FF95FF834DBDFD60FC28FCFC" baseAuthorityName="Stoliczka" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[643,967,764,788]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Psammophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blanfordanus">Psammophilus blanfordanus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
